FBIS4-8408 "dreeu071_i_94020" FBIS-EEU-94-071 Daily Report 13 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Muslims in Gorazde Deny Being Hit Muslims in Gorazde Deny Being Hit AU1304111294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 13 Apr 94 AU1304111294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Report by Mustafa Kurtovic from Gorazde] [Text] Fresh forces of the chetnik formations have arrived in [word indistinct] Ustipraca, (?Luksici) and [words indistinct]. They are being accompanied by armored-mechanized units of the former Yugoslav Peoples' Army. [Words indistinct] the free territory, from mortars and antiaircraft arms the chetniks are pounding the town's settlements of Vidkovici, [words indistinct], while from the right bank of the Drina River they are systematically firing at apartment after apartment, house after house, with snipers 80 [word indistinct]. For this reason we ask for an immediate intervention so that this town will not turn into the biggest grave in the history of mankind. The latest information claims that Karadzic's fascists are concentrating additional forces in (?Leskici), Ustipraca, and (?Luksici) and that in the planning of a new powerful offensive on Gorazde they are being assisted by war criminals Momcilo Perisic [commander of the FRY Army] and Vojislav Seselj [leader of the Serbian Radical Party]. [Words indistinct] Karadzic who visited the so-called soldiers of the Uzice corps in the area of Rogatica yesterday. The officials of the Gorazde district and commune deny all reports launched by the self-styled Serbian Radio and Television, which claim that the town center has been hit in the NATO action. Gorazde was and remains [words indistinct] fighters will always be on the defense lines and defend the sovereignty of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina until the end.
